N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 9 ยง 4231.4 - Objections; who may make objection

State Regulations

Every objection must be made by the owner, trainer or
jockey of some horse engaged in the race or by the officials of the course to
the clerk of the scales or to one of the judges, or an objection may be made by
any one of the judges. Notes
